  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PAHO PBL Adviser</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PAHO/WHO and Sightsavers collaborate to promote a Regional Program for the Prevention of Blindness in the Caribbean. Both organisations work together and with other regional entities to:
1. Support countries and stakeholders in priority setting and objectives development in line with the Strategic Framework for V2020: The Right to Sight (Caribbean Region) and according to priorities and strategies identified by PAHO and Sightsavers.
2. Provide technical cooperation and support for planning, follow up and evaluation of national eye care programs. 
3. Producing manuals, documentation and other materials to be distributed in the Region.
4. Support data collection activities and meetings which promote a cohesive regional approach to improving and increasing prevention of blindness services and public awareness</narrative>
  </description>
